title: Taiwan CPI Housing
description: CPI Housing Utilities in Taiwan decreased to 106.38 points in October from 107.40 points in September of 2022. CPI Housing Utilities in Taiwan averaged 89.56 points from 1981 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 107.40 points in September of 2022 and a record low of 62.59 points in January of 1981. This page provides - Taiwan  Cpi Housing- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Directorate-General of Budget, Accounting and Statistics, Taiwan
